                                                                                                               Conclave on HIV, AIDS
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                               
	Bhubaneswar, April 6: A group of HIV(+) women leaders today called upon political parties to make second-line anti-retroviral treatment (ART) available to those with advanced infection.        
	Around 300 women came face to face with the leaders in a conclave where a charter of demands was prepared, to be submitted to parties later.         
	As per the latest records of the Orissa State Aids Control Society, the number of reported cases of people living with HIV (PLHIV) is 9,988. Of them, 990 are living with AIDS and 773 have lost their lives A list of 7,929 PLHIV have been recommended for the Madhu Babu Pension Yojana and the rest will subsequently be included in the list.                                                                                                                                                                            
